race.comment: CAFE MILLENIUM (3) is searching for a hat-trick having won his past two impressively. He beat subsequent Group 2 winner Splash Back in Adelaide before sitting back off a fast tempo here and powering home to beat Transatlantic, who was very good behind Evaporate in the G3 Sandown Stakes. He does need the tempo on up front but if they run along, he'll be flying late. IS IT ME (5) will find this more to his liking. He's struggled in a pair of G1 races at Caulfield his past two but did win at G3 level over this route in the Spring by nearly four lengths. Could bounce back strongly here. MEDIA WORLD (9) was a good return in the G2 Bobbie Lewis over 1200m and should only improve out to 1400m here. He can roll forward and take catching. ENXUTO (11) did enough fresh in the Bobbie Lewis given he was back off a slow speed. He can elevate. VON HAUKE (10) was good from the back in the Sandown Stakes last time and can hit the frame late.
